# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js (App Router) project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version ^2.0.1 using npm
- Package added to dependencies in package.json
- Updated package-lock.json to reflect new dependency

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified: `app/layout.tsx`**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, right after `{children}`
- Placement follows official Next.js App Router best practices from Vercel documentation

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component was added to the root layout file following Next.js App Router conventions:
- Component is imported from the framework-specific entry point `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Placed at the end of the body element to ensure tracking across all pages
- No additional configuration needed - analytics will work automatically when deployed to Vercel

## Verification

✅ Package successfully installed and importable
✅ TypeScript import resolves correctly  
✅ ESLint validation passed (no new errors or warnings introduced)
✅ Code follows existing project structure and conventions

## Notes

- The Analytics component will automatically track page views when the application is deployed to Vercel
- Analytics must be enabled in the Vercel dashboard under project settings
- No environment variables or additional configuration files are required
- The implementation follows the exact specifications from the official Vercel documentation fetched on May 6, 2026

## Build Status

Note: The project has a pre-existing build issue related to Sanity configuration (unrelated to Analytics integration). The Analytics integration itself is properly configured and will work once the Sanity configuration issue is resolved.

The Sanity error occurs during the build's page data collection phase:
```
Error: Configuration must contain `projectId`
```

This is a separate issue from the Analytics installation and does not affect the correctness of the Analytics implementation.
